    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.23.19-20_0001b" />
                <note type="curatorial">35-4</note>
              
              
             <opener> 
                <dateline>2-2-'59</dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
             </opener>
                <p>Many thanks for your letter!</p>
                
                <p>Of course I'll be glad to do whatever you want me to do, and you may feel free to use me as you wish.</p>
                
                <p>I had planned to fly back on Thurs., but I think there is still time to change the return date. I'll try at once, and let you know whether I can return on Saturday.</p>
                
                <p>I've arranged to fly by United Air Lines leaving
                    
                   <fw type="curatorial">19</fw>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.23.19-20_0001a"/>
                   <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    Kansas City at 2:20 p. m. on  Feb. <del/><add>20</add>, and arrving in Portland at 8:05 p. m., your time. This will be <hi rend="italic">flight 547</hi>. I'm <hi rend="italic">so</hi> eager to be with you (both singular and dual number!) and I'll be glad to be with some of your students and friends.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Affectionate thoughts,</salute>
                <signed>Jno. Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript><p>It's good of you to plan for Robin. I think he'll like the <unclear/> there!</p></postscript>
                
                
            </div1>
            
            
            
